args:
Poor Cleo is the latest victim! Under heavy
suspicion, Norwin agrees to be locked away.
The party then stumbles across information
that leads them to believe one among them
is Scylla in disguise, but then tragedy strikes
once more!
And our freshest and hottest corpse is...

Mmm, but where would the fun be in just
spitting it out? Here's a clue: The victim is
one of the people who isn't here now.
Better go take a look around!
That leaves Cleo, Norwin, and Mikoto.
Everyone spread out and start looking.\nAnd remember, we have no proof that\nany of them has actually died.
Y-yeah, that's right! Stupid Carmen is\nprobably just running her mouth again!
Aw, your little hopes are so PITIFUL!
Cleo and Norwin said they were headed\nto a cave over in this direction...
Aw, it's just Cleo! Whew!\nMan, am I ever happy to see you.
Guys, we found Cleo! She's over...here...?
...She has no breath and no pulse.
I heard screams and came to see...\nOh, Cleo. Not you.
I'm sorry, Norwin, but it's true.
Actually, that's my question for you.\nWhat the hell happened to Cleo, Norwin?
What? Why are you asking me?
You were with Cleo yesterday afternoon,\nbut what about last night? Huh?
You can't seriously suspect me in this!
Oh, I can suspect ya in whatever I want.
Stop it, Ranzal! Norwin would never...\nI mean, he couldn't...

If I may, Your Highness, I understand your
hesitancy to cast suspicion on your friends.
But given the circumstances, Ranzal's
question is not entirely unwarranted.
Let's just hear what he has to say, yeah?\nIf he's innocent, he's got nothin' to hide!
Last night, Cleo and I went to the cave\nin order to lay out Luca's body.

Once there, we sensed a strange mana
from deep within the cave and went to
investigate. However, the caverns were
more complex than we had imagined.
She and I became separated;\nI only found my way out just now.
Lost and separated is a fairly convenient\nstory, don't you think?
Considering that you suspect me,\nit's actually quite IN-convenient.
Ya wanna try that story again, pal?\nMaybe make it a little more believable?
Enough, both of you! I'll not have anyone\ndoubting our friends without proof!
Indeed, all of this jumping at shadows\nmight be just what Carmen or Scylla\nwant us to do.
No, I understand their suspicions.\nLooking at it objectively, my story\ndoes not hold a great deal of water.
...Which means you should lock me up.
It is not just for everyone else's sake that\nI make this suggestion—being locked up\nwould allow me to rest easier as well.
There is a small basement in this hut.\nWe could put him there for the time being.
Are you sure you're all right with this?
Well, poor Norwin has been locked away,\nbut that's hardly the end of the matter.
Yeah. I mean, I know I said what I said,\nbut I don't ACTUALLY think ol' Norwin\nthere murdered Luca and Cleo.
Then why did you SAY all that stuff?!
I can't shake this feelin' there's somebody\nmessin' with us, ya know?
I think Scylla and Carmen made it clear\nthat is exactly what they're doing.
No, it ain't just this whole ＂game＂ thing—\nit's more like I'm a dog what's bein' pulled\naround on a leash I can't see.
I just keep wonderin' if there's some way\nto get a step ahead'a...whatever this is.
Sinoa, you look upset. What happened?
I searched the ruins of a nearby house\nand found this note...
Five days have passed since we were all\nforced to participate in Scylla's game.
This is likely a note left by a former\ninhabitant of this island.
We all swore we'd die rather than kill each other—\nand over the past five days, that is exactly what\nhas been taking place.
Worry ate at me. Would any of my friends slip?\nWould they choose to save themselves and\nbecome a full participant in the game?

That's when I realized one of my friends—my
live friends—wasn't who they claimed to be.
They were a fake, and my true friend had
actually died five days ago!
Scylla had disguised herself as my friend!
In other words, one of us here is not\na friend, but Scylla in disguise!
You know? That actually simplifies things.\nWe just have to find out which of us is\nScylla and then take them down.
Yes, but HOW do we do that?
Heya, Elly. Ya need somethin'?\nWhy'd ya wanna talk to me all alone?
I need to discuss something...difficult,\nand I think you may be the only person\nwho will understand what I have to say.
Is it about Scylla? Do ya know who she is?
No, I don't have the faintest idea—\nwhich is why we need to talk.
Do you recall what Carmen said about\nthe person left standing being permitted\nto leave the island?
Yeah, she said somethin' like that—\nbut I'm gonna take a big ol' pass\non doin' anything that creeper says.
And yet, if we continue as we have been,\nwe will all simply perish one by one.
If ya got a point to make here,\nI sure wish ya'd do it faster.
Don't you see, Ranzal? If only one of us\nwill be permitted to leave this island...
The morning of delicious sweet tragedy is\non us yet again! Gimme a T! Gimme an R!\nGimme an A! Gimme a—
You better BELIEVE it's again, bub!\nWe got a fresh corpse juuust waiting\nfor you!
